This paper is about digital security incident response, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The study also involves qualitative interviews with users, which relates to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and social computing (cs.SI). The paper also discusses threat models and technical development, which are relevant to cybersecurity (cs.CY) and software engineering (cs.SE).
